---
import DocsLayout from '../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro';
import PhilosophyCallout from '../../components/docs/PhilosophyCallout.astro';
---

<DocsLayout title="AI assistance" description="Cleo AI assistance behavior patterns">
  <div class="prose">
    <h1>AI assistance behavior</h1>
    <p class="page-lead">Never say "AI-powered." Show the work. Let the therapist remain the author.</p>

    <h2>Behavior</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Suggestions appear inline, not in chat bubbles</li>
      <li>Edits are always reviewable before sign — Frame 5 trust requirement</li>
      <li>No anthropomorphic assistant persona</li>
      <li>Progress during transcription is soft and linear — no chatty status messages</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Copy</h2>
    <p>We say: "Suggested revision below." We never say: "Cleo AI optimized your note."</p>

    <PhilosophyCallout>
      <p>The senior clinician colleague does not boast about tools. Neither does Cleo.</p>
    </PhilosophyCallout>
  </div>
</DocsLayout>
